      "writtenOn": "2019-05-21T19:02:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think this is broken and I don\u0027t think there\u0027s a way to fix it. It will create duplicate keys for different params.\n\nE.g.:\ntrace1 params: color_depth\u003d8888, name\u003dcar.svg\nTraceIDFromParams will return 8888:car.svg\n\ntrace2 params: config\u003d8888, name\u003dcar.svg\nTraceIDFromParams will return 8888:car.svg\n\nI discussed with Joe and he confirmed my understanding. Perf uses TraceIds like \",key1\u003dvalue1,key2\u003dvalue2,...,\". See https://skia.googlesource.com/buildbot/+/94104df6f25e4061374660b0f6132d1e104977d1/go/query/query.go",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 34,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 34,
        "endChar": 22
      },
      "revId": "cecf8a2707c82dfaacceb1f212496238f1605937",
